gov.usgs.locator

Class LocOutput

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.locator.LocOutput

  • public class LocOutput
extends java.lang.Object
    Locator outputs from an event relocation. This class is designed to contain all parameters resulting from a Locator pass. An object of this class should be handed to the output routines to be returned to the caller.

                 int stationsUsed,
                 int picksUsed,
                 double azimuthGap,
                 double azimuthGap2,
                 double minDelta,
                 java.lang.String qualityFlags)
        The following hypocenter parameters are produced by an event relocation.
        Parameters:
        originTime - Source origin time in milliseconds.
        sourceLat - Geographic source latitude in degrees.
        sourceLon - Geographic source longitude in degrees.
        sourceDepth - Source depth in kilometers.
        noStations - Number of stations associated.
        noPicks - Number of picks associated.
        stationsUsed - Number of stations used.
        picksUsed - Number of picks used.
        azimuthGap - Standard azimuthal gap in degrees.
        azimuthGap2 - Robust azimuthal gap in degrees.
        minDelta - Minimum source-receiver distance in degrees.
        qualityFlags - Location quality flags.

      • addErrors

        public void addErrors(double timeError,
                      double latError,
                      double lonError,
                      double depthError,
                      double stdError,
                      double errh,
                      double errz,
                      double avh,
                      double bayesDepth,
                      double bayesSpread,
                      double depthImport,
                      EllipAxis[] ellipsoid,
                      int exitCode)
        The following error parameters are produced by an event relocation.
        Parameters:
        timeError - Origin time error in seconds.
        latError - Latitude 90% confidence interval in kilometers.
        lonError - Longitude 90% confidence interval in kilometers.
        depthError - Depth 90% confidence interval in kilometers.
        stdError - Median travel-time residual in seconds.
        errh - Summary horizontal (tangential) error in kilometers.
        errz - Summary vertical (radial) error in kilometers.
        avh - Equivalent radius of the error ellipse in kilometers.
        bayesDepth - Final Bayesian depth in kilometers.
        bayesSpread - Final Bayesian standard deviation in kilometers.
        depthImport - Data important for the depth.
        ellipsoid - 90% error ellipsoid in kilometers.
        exitCode - Final location exit code

      • addPick

        public void addPick(java.lang.String source,
                    int pickID,
                    java.lang.String stationCode,
                    java.lang.String componentCode,
                    java.lang.String networkCode,
                    java.lang.String locationCode,
                    java.lang.String locatorPhase,
                    double residual,
                    double delta,
                    double azimuth,
                    double weight,
                    double pickImport,
                    boolean useFlag,
                    java.lang.String errorCode)
        The following parameters are produced for each pick.
        Parameters:
        source - Source of the database pick ID (optional).
        pickID - Hydra database pick ID (optional)
        stationCode - Station code.
        componentCode - Component code.
        networkCode - Network code.
        locationCode - Location code.
        locatorPhase - Final seismic phase code.
        residual - Pick residual in seconds.
        delta - Source-receiver distance in degrees.
        azimuth - Receiver azimuth (clockwise from north).
        weight - Pick weight.
        pickImport - Pick data importance.
        useFlag - True if the pick was used in the location.
        errorCode - Summary pick error code.
